President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Rita Baranwal of Pennsylvania is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Energy (Nuclear Energy) at the Department of Energy. Bernard L. McNamee of Virginia is nominated to be a Member of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Benjamin Hovland of Maryland is nominated to be a Member of the Election Assistance Commission. Joseph Bruce Hamilton of Texas and Lisa Vickers of Texas are nominated to be Members of the Board of Directors of the Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board. Lastly, Jessie Hill Roberson of Virginia is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board.